------=_NextPart_000_024F_01C83E2B.B6D5A630
Content-Type: text/plain;
	charset=&quot;us-ascii&quot;
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Babs.. I appreciate the need for validation and your argument about children
and high school kids.  As a mother that is fully engaged in my children&#39;s
school - I can guarantee you that no school in this country will allow any
device in their school to test.  If parents choose to bring their children
to a testing than that will be their decision.. right or wrong.  



It seems to me your posts are always confrontational or at minimum passive
aggressive.  Kudos to you for being a strong person who will stand up for
what you believe in.  But having read back through all your posts I find
that you indeed only post messages when you feel the need to confront people
or defend your point of view.  I think we get it now..



So here are your facts:  You strongly believe only 30 people can do this and
anyone who disagrees with this is wrapped up in their own ego.  You feel the
minibox is a rip off as well as the RS hack and that these devices will
possibly bring negative and dark forces to the rest of us if we aren&#39;t in
perfect harmony with the good. And finally that Mr. Moon is an up-standing
guy whose work and words are at best mis-understood.  



Okay we get your point. I for one think there are many versions of &quot;the
truth&quot;. There is yours, mine and theirs.  Unfortunately they never all match
up.  I wish you the best of luck in all your research and development and
hope that you will remain a positive outlet in this field.  I just ask that
the next email I read from you has something positive to add to the
research.

K



PS:  Sorry.. I know I should have dropped it but couldn&#39;t..



  _____  

From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
babiarz3
Sent: Friday, December 14, 2007 6:52 AM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: My mistruths...



Absolutely Kristin. As I said, my purpose was to clear up any
misconceptions about my honesty. I think anyone would have done the
same. Although I think it&#39;s funny that the truth gets a &quot;can we drop
it now?&quot; comment. I don&#39;t require or desire any apologies or any
replies to my post. I know that it will be read and knowing that
maybe, just maybe, someone will stop and consider the truth is enough
for me. After all, we are nothing if not honest.
Have a great day everyone and get back to work!
--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&gt; .com, &quot;Kristin
Morris&quot; &lt;ckmorris95@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Okay Babs.. You have said your peace. Can we please drop it now?
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; _____ 
&gt; 
&gt; From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&gt; .com
[mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&gt; .com] On
Behalf Of
&gt; babiarz3
&gt; Sent: Friday, December 14, 2007 6:10 AM
&gt; To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&gt; .com
&gt; Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: My mistruths...
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; I wanted to edit and add the following to my previous post but... Here
&gt; is a blatant lie by Rick Moran in an obvious attempt to discredit him.
&gt; This is from the same article...
&gt; 
&gt; &quot;There appears to be some controversy surrounding Frank&#39;s Box and
&gt; Christopher Moon, who is the publisher of Haunted Times Magazine, a
&gt; relative of George and Cathy Lutz of Amityville infamy...
&gt; 
&gt; Firstly, Christopher Moon is not now, nor will he ever be a close or
&gt; distant relative of the Lutz family. Mr. Moran lays claim to debunking
&gt; the Amityville claims and says the entire &quot;case&quot; was a fraud. Now, he
&gt; attempts to tie Christopher Moon to the supposed fraud. 
&gt; 
&gt; Now remember, this is the researcher you are supporting.
&gt; 
&gt; --- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&gt; .com,
&gt; &quot;babiarz3&quot; &lt;babiarz3@&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; A few weeks ago I posted that Rick Moran had written an article
&gt; &gt; stating that children and high school students would be part of the
&gt; &gt; testing subjects of the mini-box. Later that day the article was
&gt; &gt; replaced with a different article about the mini-box. I was told that
&gt; &gt; I was stating mis truths. I wasn&#39;t. I finally was able to locate the
&gt; &gt; missing article. I&#39;m providing a link to the entire article along with
&gt; &gt; the statement regarding our children. If the link somehow becomes
&gt; &gt; unavailable, I have done a screen shot and will provide it to whoever
&gt; &gt; asks.
&gt; &gt; Believe me when I say that this isn&#39;t to cause or stir crap. I was
&gt; &gt; basically called a liar and this clears up that misconception. If I am
&gt; &gt; banned from this group for telling the truth, than so be it. 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &quot;...it was not the question of whether the phenomenon existed to begin
&gt; &gt; with, but rather what is the phenomenon. That will require a good
&gt; &gt; deal more effort to explore and beginning in January we will be
&gt; &gt; undertaking test sessions all over north and east Texas as well as
&gt; &gt; other national locations with a wide variety of folks to see what
&gt; &gt; happens within the group dynamic. The testing will include folks who
&gt; &gt; are both believers and non-believers, skeptics, critics, other
&gt; &gt; researchers, children, high school students, college and grad
&gt; &gt; students, and senior citizens to name a few categories.&quot;
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; http://www.asup-
&lt;http://www.asup- &lt;http://www.asup-inc.org/pages/editorial11-29-07.html&gt;
inc.org/pages/editorial11-29-07.html&gt;
&gt; inc.org/pages/editorial11-29-07.html
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Are you willing to &quot;see what happens&quot; with our children?
&gt; &gt;
&gt;




